alse}}],"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":0,"can_be_copied":1,"can_remove_fork":1,"forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"access":{"can_view":1,"can_remove":0,"can_add":0,"can_edit":0,"can_publish":0,"can_get_doi":0,"can_share":1,"can_move":1,"can_move_outside":1,"can_transfer":1,"can_download":1,"is_locked":0},"guid":"A450AB402E4611EA895211B47B6D1758","steps":[{"id":866364,"guid":"5AA749D02E4711EA895211B47B6D1758","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E846C7B313BE456DBC861A3BE158137D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Pre-treatment of sample"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"5E5BFD56117848B1A837F4D86EA497D7","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Water samples are collected in 5L sterile containers and transported to the laboratory. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Six samples are collected at each site to give a total of 30 litres per sample.\n<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">The water samples are processed using the CapE system by placing the submersible pump into the pooled water samples.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">NOTE: these first two steps might vary according to the each partner and systems available to collect water samples.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":866365,"guid":"6D6EB8F02E4711EA895211B47B6D1758","previous_id":866364,"previous_guid":"5AA749D02E4711EA895211B47B6D1758","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"BDBB6133E62C498192061F7AA9C40923","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Pre-treatment of sample"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4694E36E5358470FA7C24980621C761C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>The 0.45\u03bcm filter is folded up using sterile forceps and placed in 100mL of <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Buffered Peptone Water (BPW) <\/span><span>for <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">18-24 <\/span><span>hours incubation at <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">42 \u030aC \u00b1 1\u00b0C<\/span><span>. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">NOTE: Place all filters used per sample (30L) in the one 100mL BPW container.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":866367,"guid":"B3E4E6602E4711EA895211B47B6D1758","previous_id":866365,"previous_guid":"6D6EB8F02E4711EA895211B47B6D1758","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"AB6642549C144822B304930539426BE2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Streak a SCAi medium agar plate"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C9A185358AE04C4A9EBFDB3FEFE60640","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Following 18-24h incubation, using a 10\u03bcl loop, streak for single colonies onto the surface of a small petri dish (90 mm) of <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">SCAI medium <\/span><span>and incubate at <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">37\u00b0C \u00b1 1\u00b0C<\/span><span> for <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">48h \u00b1 1 h.<\/span><span><\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Sometimes, typical colonies (yellow, moist, dome-shaped) can be recognized after 24h culture on plates, but 48 h is much better to discriminate <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella-<\/span><span>looking colonies from other ones (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">E. coli<\/span><span> colonies are typically white because they do not use inositol).   <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>It can happen that the medium, which should initially be blue, turns completely yellow, when there are many inositol-fermenting colonies (typically <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella<\/span><span>). In these cases, discriminating yellow colonies is less easy. Diluting before streaking could help in these cases. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":866370,"guid":"E2038A602E4711EA895211B47B6D1758","previous_id":866367,"previous_guid":"B3E4E6602E4711EA895211B47B6D1758","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"6CA034015BA94C7FA3D646F631EB7599","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Purification and identification of suspect Klebsiella colonies"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"04C237F3EF9D45C98F9FCFD0621E99DE","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Typical <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella<\/span><span> spp. colonies are yellow on SCAI medium.   \n<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Select suspect <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella<\/span><span> colonies for subculture and bacterial identification. \n<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Streak the selected colonies onto the surface of a non-selective agar medium (e.g., LB or TSA) in a manner which will allow isolated colonies to develop. Incubate plates at 37 \u00b0C \u00b1 1\u00b0C for 24 h \u00b1 1 h.   <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">NOTE: If colonies are numerous and close to each other, re-isolate the colony on another SCAi agar plate to control for purity. Incubate for up to 48h.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":866371,"guid":"EF31B7702E4711EA895211B47B6D1758","previous_id":866370,"previous_guid":"E2038A602E4711EA895211B47B6D1758","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D01977108B3B4FB3B50F37A4B1278CE6","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Purification and identification of suspect Klebsiella colonies"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C235D9AF11064358ADD138A6B66921E8","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Determine species of purified suspect <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">K. pneumoniae<\/span><span> colonies using MALDI-TOF mass spectrometry and\/or species-specific PCR.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":866372,"guid":"F574A7002E4711EA895211B47B6D1758","previous_id":866371,"previous_guid":"EF31B7702E4711EA895211B47B6D1758","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"286F90B69E2F448D9D0CAD8F941CDBC5","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Mixed-colony storage for future studies (additional)"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4DAAE0DCE96D4E8FA9661BEAB826AA31","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">If desired, after picking selected colonies, sweep the remaining SCAi plate content and freeze it at -80\u00b0C (e.g., for mixed colonies sequencing) using CryoBank tubes or equivalent (e.g., in house BHI + 15% glycerol medium).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":866373,"guid":"FBCEC8102E4711EA895211B47B6D1758","previous_id":866372,"previous_guid":"F574A7002E4711EA895211B47B6D1758","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0110B40A3D32416AA720BE6B37B89E02","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Storage of bacterial strains"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F581BF27807C477B8F24A1635CCF5AE7","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Freeze strains confirmed as Klebsiella pneumoniae (or its related species, which also grow on SCAi) at -80\u00b0C using CryoBank tubes or equivalent (e.g. BHI + 15% glycerol medium).<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">If several morphotypes are available, you may want to store one colony per morphotype.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[{"id":348952,"mol_weight":0,"name":"myo-inositol","linfor":"","url":"http:\/\/","sku":"I5125-50 g","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Sigma Aldrich","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/sigmaaldrich.com","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":17},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":348953,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Simmons citrate","linfor":"","url":"http:\/\/","sku":"64834-500g","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"BioRad Sciences","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/www.bio-rad.com\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":272},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">This protocol is intended for isolation of Klebsiella strains from water samples. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>It is derived from the initial description of the SCAi medium (van Kregten E, Westerdaal, N. A. C., and Willers, J. M. N. New, simple medium for selective recovery of <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella pneumoniae<\/span><span> and <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella oxytoca<\/span><span> from human feces. Journal of Clinical Microbiology. 1984;20:936-41) and its validation across a diversity of <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella <\/span><span>strains (Passet V, Brisse S. 2015. Association of tellurite resistance with hypervirulent clonal groups of <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Klebsiella pneumoniae<\/span><span>. J Clin Microbiol. 53(4):1380-2). <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">The protocol entails enrichment using Buffered Peptone Water (BPW), and plating on SCAi (Simmons Citrate with Inositol) agar.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">This protocol was optimized by the MedVetKlebs consortium. <\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1578323582}